    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>India's Creaky Courts</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Barbara C King letter says India's legal system as described in June 1 article bears comparison with the British legal system described in Dickens's Bleak House</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''In India, the Wheels of Justice Hardly Move'' (front page, June 1):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''In India, the Wheels of Justice Hardly Move'' (front page, June 1):</p>
        <p>Dickens! thou shouldst be living at this hour. How he would have loved this version of the interminable Jarndyce v. Jarndyce lawsuit in ''Bleak House.'' Here is yet another wonderful instance of life imitating art.</p>
        <p>BARBARA C. KING  Locust Valley, N.Y., June 2, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
